  FEATURES OF LANGUAGE
  argument - a conversation or discussion in which two or more people disagree, often angrily .
  
                     a reason or set of reasons that somebody uses to show that something is true or correct.
					  

LANGUAGE SKILLS

accent - [singular] a special importance that is given to something.

articulate  - (of a person) good at expressing ideas or feelings clearly in words.

articulate adjective - (of a person) good at expressing ideas or feelings clearly in words.

broad -  including a great variety of people or things.

              if somebody has a broad accent (= a way of pronouncing the words of a language), you can hear very easily which area they come from
			  
			  if somebody gives a broad hint, they make it very clear what they are thinking or what they want.
			  
brush up - to quickly improve a skill, especially when you have not used it for a time.

coherent - (of ideas, thoughts, arguments, etc.) logical and well organized; easy to understand and clear.


drill - a way of learning something by means of repeated exercises
        
         the correct or usual way to do something		